data.name: Spicy Grilled Chicken Bowl
data.quickTastyDescription: A zesty, protein-packed bowl with grilled chicken seasoned to perfection, served over a bed of rice and topped with fresh veggies.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the grill or a grill pan over medium-high heat.
In a bowl, mix olive oil, spicy seasoning blend, salt, and pepper. Coat the chicken breast with the mixture.
Grill the chicken for about 6-7 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and juices run clear.
While the chicken is grilling, prepare your rice according to package instructions if not already done.
Once the chicken is done, let it rest for a few minutes, then slice it thinly.
In serving bowls, layer the cooked rice, grilled chicken, sliced bell peppers, corn, and avocado.
Top with fresh cilantro and a squeeze of lime juice for added flavor.
data.detailedName: Spicy Grilled Chicken Bowl with Rice and Veggies
